# Finish every code task with checks and a commit

After completing any task that changes code, always run these commands in order:

```bash
./vendor/bin/pint --dirty
vendor/bin/phpstan analyse --memory-limit=1G
./vendor/bin/phpunit
```

- Fix any failures before reporting the task as done.
- If Pint changes files, re-run PHPStan and tests.

Then commit all relevant changes before finishing the task.

- Do not leave completed work uncommitted.
- Use conventional commit prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`, `style:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, etc.).
- Write a concise message focused on the why, not a dump of file names.
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, etc.).
- Do not push unless the user explicitly asks.
